The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Tuesday, June 08, 2004 				 Sindh chief minister quits 
																								Karachi, June 7 (Reuters): The chief minister of Pakistans key southern province of Sindh resigned today following a wave of militant and political violence in Karachi last month that killed more than 60 people.																								Even before Mays violence, Ali Mohammad Maharter was under pressure to go from members of his own ruling Pakistan Muslim League and its allies unhappy with his performance. 
